	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100013596793865><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100013596793865>WHAT I DID</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100013596793865#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 10th 11:32 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, this might not be the best way but this is what I did,<br>1-5 Gfay <br>Got port to WC, run like heck to fp<br>5-8 solo pumas and rattle snakes in front of ec tunnel for decent exp<br><br>8-12 orc group<br>12-15 Dervish in WC<br>15-20 Orcs in High Hold<br>20-22 Tried Lake of Ill omen but way to much lag, so I went to Sk and hunted Gnolls from the spires<br>22-28 Group to kill the gnolls and then about 28 or so you MIght be able to kite them, if you pay attention to what your doing they hit hard and fast but drop decent loot<br><br>29-30 Caught ride to Velious and Invised all the way to Thug, There I grouped to kill Tizmak, and several FG's <br>Velium Sells pretty much the same as FS and drops off of tizmak, plus the Tizmak armor.<br>I found that the gnolls have a lower spawn rate then the things you find in Lake of Ill omen but having less people and less lag was better for me. Not saying this is the best way just my way.<br>Regnon Plainswalker<br>Druid of the 30th season<br>Bertoxx Server<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
