	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've rarely ever kited. Most of the time I am partnered, so we end up using root/nuke technique (since he is a mage). The only time I've really kited is when pulling, if I stop to DD it or DoT on its way. <br><br>Have you tried fear kiting? We can do this with animals, like lions. snare it, cast panic animal and run after it killing it. You can use befriend animal on a green kitty (last longer on greens. I had befriend last seemingly AGES on a kitty once. it was cool), snare the one you want, cast fear and tell pet to attack, DoT it with Swarm, then run after it DDing until it dies. Recast fear as needed. <br><br>Oh, one idea. I have found this incredibly useful soloing Kobolds, who hit hard for thier lvl. Cast your Stinging Swarm DoT as soon as you snare. This will do damage until it wears off. If you are snaring and not rooting, don't use Cascade of Hail, and they will end up moving out of range of the damage.<br><br>Just some ideas. Like I said, I don't kite much right now, so I can't really offer any secrets of kiting. <br><br>Tatiyanna<br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
