	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just started a Wood Elf Druid about 2 weeks ago, she is now level 20 and parked in LOIO. I have taken her along the same journey as my Ranger. I do not know if this will help or answer your question. lvl 1-12 I did in GFay and Crushbone, I did the pixie dust quests, the batwing quest, and the Crushbone belts. at 12 I ventured over to Oasis, and was snatche dup in a group the day I arrived...fighting yellow caiman and crocs, I stayed there until level 20, returned to kelethin after getting my first port spell sin West Commons..got rest of my spells then hopped the boat to Firona Vie, Camo'd and ran to LOIO. I will stay there till about 30 or 31. there are many things you can snare kite there, or believe me if playing healer is your thing, groups will snatch you up, for fast experience all you have to do is keep em healed. From LOIO, I plan to hit Frontier Mountain till around 34...then I will be off to Rath Mountain,,,for Hill Giants, while experience is steady..it is not the best, but money can be made quickly from them , cuz we all know how expensive Druid spells are to obtain, and lets face it, if you port all day long, you are not enhancing your other skills, such as defense, offense, and weapons, alos for a twist, level 29 is a good time to venture to velious and learn how to quad kite, by taking on the Tizmarks there, start with one...and work your way up to four..will help you get out of that level 35 hell quickly...smiles....just my humble opionion, I am following my Rangers path. Hope that helped in some small way...and just wanted to say everyone seems so knowledgable on Druids, this site has helped me in figuring out some of the difference in Rangers and Druids, get use to Track it can become an invaluable tool...<br><br>Senzimil (Krystline) Druid of 20th Season/Ranger of 40th<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
