	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, for those of you who don't know this, and trust me, I was one too for a long time HARMONY IS NOT THE SAME AS MEZZ!!&nbsp;&nbsp;I died several times before I realized this. What harmony does is to reduce the aggro range of a mob till it is almost nothing. Two mobs will have to be practically on top of one another to bring one after you have harmonied them. As to why you bring in more than one mob when you pull after you harmony, you can't attack the one you harmonied first. This will break harmony on all the mobs. This is a great spell once you know what your doing. Good luck to you in your hunts, and may Karana bring you riches.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
