	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm thinking of starting a new Druid Character does anyone have any tips or advice as to choosing the race or what do do when i start? <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=99970815687796></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99970815687796><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=99970815687796>RE: New Character</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=99970815687796#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=79214><span id=Scholar>Ravensveil</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>243 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 5th 12:42 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.11]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Tee hee, that send button get's people ever time. *wink*<br><br>Alright, at the risk of repeating myself, but I don't really mind ;)<br><br>The best race for Druids, IMO, is the Wood-elf. We are just the cutest, I think. Well, we women are. I don't know if you're going to make it male or female. I will say that Female Woodelves seem to get ALOT of attention, so if you don't mind the flirting it can really pay off.<br><br>Hey! Whatdaya want?!<br><br>What to do. Well, you need wisdom, so make sure it is nice and high. Um, i think that agility and dex are your other two major traits. Maybe it was intellignence and agility. I don't remember. I am pretty sure that Agility affects your casting some how. I KNOW wisdom does, and it affects your mana. I think that intelligence affects your downtime when meditating. it also affects how quickly you learn skills.<br><br>You've created it. So, what to do? <br><br>Well, once you turn in your note, start killing things. you'll die alot. Don't lose heart. As soon as you can get that blast of fire spell thingy (not flame lick. you won't have component for it yet. But when you can buy a fire beetle eye, get the spell). <br><br>Lvl 1-2 Kill Bats and Skeles and Wasps, just be careful not that the wasps and skeles don't swarm you. Try to save your Bat Wings and Bone Chips<br><br>2-3 start taking on Orc Pawns and Pixie Tricksters and Widow Hatchlings. These can be tough, but they will be easier as you get into lvl 3. Keep saving Batwings, Bone Chips and also spiderling silks, Orc Hatchets, and Pixie Dust.<br><br>3-5 more of the same above. You'll find you can take on multiple of the bats, skeles, and wasps.<br><br>Ok. All those things that I told you to hold on to and not sell:<br><br>Batwings. You can do one of two things. If you want to make money, sell batwings 20 at a time to players for about 2plat a stack. <br>If you want experience, turn them in to Niola Impholder in the mage guild in Felwith<br><br>Bonechips. I suggest not going the money route with them right now. you'll have chances to do that later. Instead, turn them in to the head of the Clerics Guild in Felwith for xp and faction. You want to do this so you can get the Tunare quests later.<br><br>Orc Hatchet and Pixie Dust can be turned in to people at the Ranger's Guild. Again for XP and faction. Sometimes items.<br><br>Avoid the bladed weapon quest from your guild master. I have never been able to complete this quest without buying the items, and you spend more money than the quest is worth. There is no quest following it, unlike the bone chips, so it's a waste.<br><br>Every time you go to Felwith, talk to the mage by Faydark's Bane. Take the note to Jakum Webdancer in Kelethin. Easy xp and gold. Worth it, since it is a trip you are making ANYWAY<br><br>Now, onto the next lvls<br><br>At lvl 5 you start getting what are REALLY our defining spells. Don't toss away snare, though. It took me a while to learn, that spell is great.<br><br>At lvl 5-7, start finding groups for orc hill. Collect Cent Belts and bank them. Don't do anything with them yet. Just bank them. You can start grouping for orc hill as early as lvl 4, but only if you are confident in your ability and the group.<br><br>Once you hit lvl 7, you've gotten a good amount of belts saved up. Make a run to Kaladim in ButcherBlock Mountains and turn them in to Conloe in the warrior's guild for faction, xp and armor. If you've gotten the money to upgrade your armor, sell it. It all sells well to merchants. Depending on how many belts you managed to collect, you can easily send yourself up through lvl 8. If not to 9, then well on your way.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Okay, gate back home.<br><br>Find a group and go into Crushbone.<br><br>You can play in Crushbone all the way through lvl 10 if you like. <br>Stick to bridge area for a lvl or two, then move into Slaver cave (NOT PITS) area. Free slaves for faction and xp. Kill things. Be mindful of Lego's.<br><br>By lvl 10, you are probably tired of orcs and don't want to see another for a LONG time. That's fine. <br><br>You've also figured out that in alot of cases you make a good puller. There are times where you'll want a tank to pull. But if the pull requires delicacy, you are the best if an Enchanter isn't around. Save your belts. Bank them.<br><br>Now, make sure you've bought ward summoned.<br><br>lvl 10-12 group and eventually solo in Steamfont. With Treeform you can start soloing elementals and drakes. Otherwise group for them and the mino cave. Druids can get into the mino groups EASILY.<br><br>lvl 12-14 group (not too large) and take on the Nybright sisters in Lesser Faydark. They are a quest involving the Cleric Guild in Felwith and the drunkard. You can also group for Unrest. Good loot. Both are an easy way to afford your lvl 14 spells.<br><br>At 14, you can go back to Crushbone if you want and kite Lego's. There is a cave by the Lego camp that is accessible from the slaver camps. This is a good place to kite them. It is best done with a mage partner, IMO. snare him. Kit him down the cave. DD him if you want. Once he is in range of the mage, root him. Back up. let pet tank and the two of you nuke him. Beautiful. You want to do this and collect the Lego Pads when they drop. A few diligent hours will net you a backpack full some nights.<br><br>Now, those extra belts you've been collecting. If you want you can turn them in, but by now, xp is nominal. <br><br>Belts sell for 5gp - 1pl a peice. Sweet. Lego pads go for i think 2-4pl a peice. You can make LOTS of money auctioning them. And, if people accuse you of farming, target them and type /emote sticks tongue out at %t "pthbt" and then tell them that you've been saving them since lvl 8 or 9. :)<br><br>Alright, now, make sure you have Expulse summoned. Forget Steam. you are going to Lavastorm. You are hunting Lava Crawlers and fending off fire eles and sprites that agro you. I recommend a mage partner. Mages and druids work real well together because a mage comes with tank in tow.<br><br>Lava crawlers are nice xp. Lava storm is actually best if you hit it around lvl 12. But it will carry you through to 15. <br><br>Lvl 15-16. Tee hee. It is time for every lightie's favorite past time. Yes. HUNTING DARKELF GUARDS.<br><br>There is a guard at the lavastorm entrance who is easy pickings. Practice on him a while. You will do best, again, with the mage. He sometimes resists snare, but rarely resists fire and hail.<br><br>Once you've gotten used to fighting a guard, find someone in thier twenties who will split the bridge with you. Let the twenty+ person(s) take the higher conning guards. You and your friends take the lower ones. For the bridge guards, you really want to add one or two more people. <br><br>These are great because hey spawn quickly.<br><br>Once you hit lvl 16, I really suggest getting yourself over to Stone Brunt. It is a really great zone and can carry you through your 20's easily if you want. For a change of pace you can fight inside the warrens, which is great xp. also, fighting kobolds gets you erudite and hertic faction. Which means that you will soon NOT be KoS when passing through Paineel and you'll be on better terms with the Erudites (like we really care).<br><br>I suggest travelling any time withing these stages, beginning at lvl 5. If you can make it to Qeynos, which you can at lvl 5, I've done, it, get a bind and lvl up to maybe 6 and go after cubert and the dress. Turn it in to zamel and get some earrings. You probably want alteast a guide to the right spot. Getting lost here is really bad.<br><br>Alright, so that is my advice to get you where I am. <br><br>Have fun.<br><br>Tatiyanna<br>Mommy Druid of Ravensveil<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
