	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 5th 10:45 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Go to Steamfont. Make sure you have Treeform and Ward summoned. Watch where spawns come. Find a spot where you can pull what you want and Treeform. You can pull Elementals to you. Or Drakes. Maybe harpies if they con a lvl you can handle solo.<br><br>You med faster in Treeform and get other pluses I don't remember. This is great loot and xp for this lvl.<br><br>You can also get into a group fairly easily as a druid for Mino caves. I can't even remember how many times I had people trying to pillage me out of my current group for the mino caves.<br><br>Play with steam for a couple of levels. Once you are around lvl 12, find a partner or two and play with the Nybright sisters in lesser fay for the drunkard's quest. You can also start getting into groups to take on yard trash in Unrest. Both of these are great xp. Unrest is really dangerous but once you get the hang of it, really worth it. DO NOT camp in the front. I can't stress that enough. Camp the back yard. You can avoid most trains there.<br><br>Around Lvl 12 you can also head over to Lavastorm. Again, ward summoned is great here because everything but the basks (which you want to avoid like the plague), rock dervishes, and drakes are summoned. The Lava crawlers can be taken down easily with a partner (always bring a caster like a mage) and yeild bloodstones about 1 in 3 kills. Good ratio for a jewel drop. They also sometimes drop bloodstone rings. Or was that the drakes? anyway, there is good loot.<br><br>All the zones I mentioned are GREAT xp and GREAT loot, which is always a bonus cause lvl 14 spells taint cheap.<br><br>I'd stay away from Oasis. I found it to be a phenominal waste of time. Oh, if you hit Lavastorm, find a cleric to team with and hit befallen. The first level will probably be a sleeper, but you should be able to find some stuff. It's a neat dungeon, but it is indoors, so be aware of that. <br><br>Tatiyanna<br>Mommy Druid of Ravensveil<br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
