	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK I hope this helps I just made a druid about 2 weeks ago and made lvl 22 last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;What I did from 10-14 was kill wisps.  Kill as many wisps as possible get the greater lightstones and lightstones.  Once you get a backpack or so full of GLS and LS pay the 15pp for a port to NK and ask for a sow and camo.  Head NW to the gypsy camp and give the stones to the gypsy who gives you the quest when you hail her.  I was getting a full blue and then some for each gls and a good piece of a blue for normal lightstones.  You can sell the books from the GLS for 6-7pp each and the ls get a few silver not a big deal the EXP is important.  That got me enough money and exp to make lvl 14 and buy all of my spells.  At lvl 14 I went straight to lavastorm.  Kill even,  yellow and red flame elementals lava crawlers imps and anything else that is summoned.  I did this to lvl 18.  I made 18th in 2 days about 2-4 hours a day camping by the najena zone in case things go bad.  There seem to be a lot of spawns there to keep you busy. The loot here is OK you get bloodstones and words.  Bloodstones can get you 3 gold or so each at the druids or gypsies in the same zone.  At lvl 18 I went to NK and killed griffawns and anything else blue or even to me to make lvl 19.  At lvl 19 I got new spells and headed to EK killing Crag Spiders.  Made lvl 20 in abuot 3-4 hours.  At lvl 20 I discovered a quest in Lake Rathe that gets you over 1 full blue bubble each time.  What you do is go to the island SE of the first one from the SK zone.  There is a little gnome guy who starts the mage epic.  Hail him and start the quest.  Bind here and port to WC go find the roaming guy in the back forget his name but the quest tells you and give him the coin.  Gate back and do the same thing over and over.  I made 2 lvls in about 6 hours of doing this and maxed out tracking and my casting spells.  This quest supposedly takes you to 29th,  but I am not so sure it will be too good after 24th.  I hope this helps.  <br>Ichytharus 22nd halfling druid of Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
